   <concept id="FAR_15_304"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">15.304</ph> Evaluation factors and
significant subfactors.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d894e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d916e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                   The award decision is based on
evaluation factors and significant subfactors that are tailored
to the acquisition.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d916e15" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                   Evaluation
factors and significant subfactors must-</p>
               <ol id="d894e32" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e21" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Represent the
key areas of importance and emphasis to be considered in the source
selection decision; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e26" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Support
meaningful comparison and discrimination between and among competing
proposals.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d916e31" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                   The evaluation
factors and significant subfactors that apply to an acquisition
and their relative importance, are within the broad discretion of
agency acquisition officials, subject to the following requirements:</p>
               <ol id="d894e62" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e37" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d916e42" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2017-010?>Price
or cost to the Government shall be evaluated in every source selection
(<xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2018-title10/html/USCODE-2018-title10-subtitleA-partIV-chap137-sec2305.htm"
                                       format="html"
                                       scope="external"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2305</xref>(a)(3)(A)(ii)and <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2018-title41/html/USCODE-2018-title41-subtitleI-divsnC-chap33-sec3306.htm"
                                       format="html"
                                       scope="external"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3306</xref>(c)(1)(B)(also
see part  36 for architect-engineer contracts), subject
to the exception listed in paragraph (c)(1)(ii)(A) of this section
for use by DoD, NASA, and the Coast Guard.<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 15.304 by revising paragraph (c)(1) and?></ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d916e56" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">In accordance with <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2018-title10/html/USCODE-2018-title10-subtitleA-partIV-chap137-sec2305.htm"
                                       format="html"
                                       scope="external"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 2305</xref>(a)(3),
for DoD, NASA, and the Coast Guard—</ph>
                           </p>
                           <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d916e66" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">The
contracting officer may choose not to include price or cost as an
evaluation factor for award when a solicitation—</ph>
                                 </p>
                                 <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p id="d916e73" class="- topic/p ">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">Has an estimated value above
the simplified acquisition threshold;</ph>
                                       </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p id="d916e79" class="- topic/p ">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">Will result in multiple-award
contracts (see subpart  <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                                   class="- topic/xref "
                                                   base="FAR_Subpart_16_5"
                                                   href="Subpart_16.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_16_5">16.5</xref>) that are for the same or
similar services; and</ph>
                                       </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p id="d916e88" class="- topic/p ">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">States that the Government
intends to make an award to each and all qualifying offerors (see
2.101).</ph>
                                       </p>
                                    </li>
                                 </ol>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d916e94" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">If the contracting officer
chooses not to include price or cost as an evaluation factor for
the contract award, in accordance with paragraph (c)(1)(ii)(A) of
this section, the contracting officer shall consider price or cost
as one of the factors in the selection decision for each order placed
under the contract.</ph>
                                 </p>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d916e100" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">The exception in paragraph
(c)(1)(ii)(A) of this section shall not apply to solicitations for
multiple-award contracts that provide for sole source orders pursuant
to section 8(a) of the Small Business Act (<xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2018-title15/html/USCODE-2018-title15-chap14A-sec637.htm"
                                             format="html"
                                             scope="external"
                                             class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C. 637</xref>(a)).</ph>
                                 </p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e109" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                         The quality
of the product or service shall be addressed in every source selection
through consideration of one or more non-cost evaluation factors
such as past performance, compliance with solicitation requirements,
technical excellence, management capability, personnel qualifications,
and prior experience (<xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2018-title10/html/USCODE-2018-title10-subtitleA-partIV-chap137-sec2305.htm"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2305</xref>(a)(3)(A)(ii)
and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3306</xref>(c)(1)(A));
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e120" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                     </p>
                     <ol id="d894e105" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d916e125" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                               Past
performance, except as set forth in paragraph (c)(3)(iii) of this
section, shall be evaluated in all source selections for negotiated
competitive acquisitions expected to exceed the simplified acquisition
threshold.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d916e130" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                               For solicitations
that are not set aside for small business concerns, involving consolidation
or bundling, that offer a significant opportunity for subcontracting,
the contracting officer shall include a factor to evaluate past
performance indicating the extent to which the offeror attained
applicable goals for small business participation under contracts
that required subcontracting plans (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.637(d)(4)(G)(ii)</xref>).</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d916e138" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              
                              
                               Past
performance need not be evaluated if the contracting officer documents
the reason past performance is not an appropriate evaluation factor
for the acquisition.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e143" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                         For solicitations,
that are not set aside for small business concerns, involving consolidation
or bundling, that offer a significant opportunity for subcontracting,
the contracting officer shall include proposed small business subcontracting
participation in the subcontracting plan as an evaluation factor
(<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">15 U.S.C.637(d)(4)(G)(i)</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e151" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        
                        
                         If telecommuting
is not prohibited, agencies shall not unfavorably evaluate an offer
that includes telecommuting unless the contracting officer executes
a written determination in accordance with FAR <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref "
                              base="FAR_7_108"
                              href="7.108.dita#FAR_7_108">7.108</xref>(b).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d916e159" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                   All factors
and significant subfactors that will affect contract award and their
relative importance shall be stated clearly in the solicitation
(<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2305(a)(2)(A)(i)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3306(b)(1)(A)</xref>)
(see <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref "
                        base="FAR_15_204_5"
                        href="15.204-5.dita#FAR_15_204_5">15.204-5</xref>(c)). The rating method need not be disclosed in the
solicitation. The general approach for evaluating past performance
information shall be described.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d916e173" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2017-010?>Unless the exception at paragraph
(c)(1)(ii)(A) of this section applies, the solicitation shall also
state, at a minimum, whether all evaluation factors other than cost
or price, when combined, are—<?FM MARKER [Why] paragraph (e) introductory text.?></ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d894e191" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e182" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Significantly
more important than cost or price;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e187" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Approximately
equal to cost or price; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d916e192" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Significantly
less important than cost or price (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C.2305(a)(3)(A)(iii)</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C.3306(c)(1)(C)</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
